#: src/network-proxies.md:1
msgid "Network proxies"
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:3
msgid ""
"Enterprise networks often don't have direct outside HTTP access, but enforce "
"the use of proxies. If you're on such a network, you can request that "
"`rustup` uses a proxy by setting its URL in the environment. In most cases, "
"setting `https_proxy` should be sufficient. Commands may differ between "
"different systems and shells:"
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:9
msgid "On a Unix-like system with a shell like **bash** or **zsh**:"
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:11 src/network-proxies.md:15
msgid "socks5://proxy.example.com:1080"
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:13
msgid ""
"On Windows [**Command Prompt (cmd)**](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cmd.exe):"
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:17
msgid ""
"On Windows [**PowerShell**](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PowerShell) (or "
"**PowerShell Core**):"
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:19
msgid "\"socks5://proxy.example.com:1080\""
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:21
msgid ""
"Replace `socks5://proxy.example.com:1080` with `http://proxy.example."
"com:8080` when an HTTP proxy is used instead."
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:24
msgid ""
"If you need a more complex setup, `rustup` supports the convention used by "
"the **curl** program, documented in the ENVIRONMENT section of [its manual "
"page](https://curl.se/docs/manpage.html#:~:text=Environment,-"
"The%20environment%20variables)."
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:28
msgid ""
"The use of `curl` is presently **deprecated**, however it can still be used "
"by providing the `RUSTUP_USE_CURL` environment variable, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:32
msgid "1"
msgstr ""

#: src/network-proxies.md:35
msgid ""
"Note that some versions of `libcurl` apparently require you to drop the "
"`http://` or `https://` prefix in environment variables. For example, "
"`export http_proxy=proxy.example.com:1080` (and likewise for HTTPS). If you "
"are getting an SSL `unknown protocol` error from `rustup` via `libcurl` but "
"the command-line `curl` command works fine, this may be the problem."
msgstr ""
